m_vList.NAME: Heavy Ore
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An ore containing a very heavy and solid mineral that can be mined from the "Ward of Brambles" in Ribrum etc.

m_vList.NAME: Iron Ore
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An ore containing a lot of iron that can be mined from the rocks in Albus etc. It can be used as daily necessities or the material to make weapons.

m_vList.NAME: Obsidian
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A volcanic ore that can glow in the dark. It can be mined from the rocks in Albus etc., and is often used as the material to make Bombs.

m_vList.NAME: Gravistone
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A marvelous ore so light that it can float on water. It can be mined from the "Hideout of the Dardala Company" in Ateria etc.

m_vList.NAME: Fest
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A white ore that can be found on the shore in Eruleum etc. It's very solid and is hard to process.

m_vList.NAME: Ice-Cold Stone
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A beautiful ore that is prone to emit heat. It can be mined from the rocks in Ribrum etc., and can be used as a synthesis material after being processed.

m_vList.NAME: Lava Ore
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An ore which contains extreme heat like lava. It requires skills to process it.

m_vList.NAME: Mermaid's Tear
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A drop-shaped ore that resembles the tear of a mermaid. It has a pearly luster and is a very popular ornament.

m_vList.NAME: Broken Jadestone
m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] A mysterious substance that can only be gained for a limited time. It's a rare material that can be used to make Jadestone Hair Ornaments.

m_vList.NAME: Rainbow Corundum
m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] A mysterious substance that can only be gained for a limited time. It's a rare material that can be used to make Jadestone Armor.

m_vList.NAME: Bressislian Mystery Stone
m_vList.DESC: [Special Material] A mysterious material gained from the Dimensional Vortex. It's an ingredient for the Bressislian gear.

m_vList.NAME: Mana Cluster
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A crystal that gives off an intimidating power. It's a rare material that can be mined in Ateria.

m_vList.NAME: Diamond
m_vList.DESC: [Material] This beautiful stone is said to be the hardest ore. It can be made into extremely strong armor and shields.

m_vList.NAME: Crystal
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A transparent ore that can be mined in the "Goblins' Den" and the "Fairyland". It can be made into rare gear etc.

m_vList.NAME: Mithril
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A very precious ore that gives off a silver luster and has high rigidity and magical power.

m_vList.NAME: Fluorspar
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A mysterious crystal that emits dim light like fireflies. It can be mined from the "Hideout of the Dardala Company" in Ateria etc.

m_vList.NAME: Unmelted Ice
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A mysterious ice that won't melt. It's dropped by the monster "Element of Hails" that appears in Eruleum at night.

m_vList.NAME: Essence of the Dark Night
m_vList.DESC: [Special Material] A mysterious material gained from the Dimensional Vortex. It's an ingredient for the Dark Night gear.

m_vList.NAME: Puni Essence
m_vList.DESC: [Ingredient] A mysterious Puni-Puni-shaped lump that looks soft but is extraordinarily hard.

m_vList.NAME: Sea Glass
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A colorful piece of glass of sea that is as beautiful as a gem. It's often found on the shore of Eruleum etc.

m_vList.DESC: [Ingredient] An ingredient used to synthesize gear using the Autumn Treant materials.

m_vList.DESC: [Special Material] A mysterious material gained from the Dimensional Vortex. It's an ingredient for the Halloween gear.

m_vList.DESC: [Special Material] A mysterious material gained from the Dimensional Vortex. It's an ingredient for the Halloween gear.

m_vList.DESC: [Special Material] A mysterious material gained from the Dimensional Vortex. It's an ingredient for the Halloween gear.

m_vList.DESC: [Special Material] A mysterious material gained from the Dimensional Vortex. It's an ingredient for the Halloween gear.

m_vList.NAME: Primordial Ash
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A rare material dropped by the rare monster "Golden Puni" living in the depths of dungeons.

m_vList.NAME: Scale of Stars
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A scale that gives off an intimidating power. There are records that they were gathered in Eruleum.

m_vList.NAME: Milk
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Goat's milk has a strange taste, but it's nutritious. It seems to be used to make various Cuisine in mountainous areas.

m_vList.NAME: Honey
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Viscous, thick and sweet honey that can be gathered from the beehives on the apple trees in Albus, etc.

m_vList.NAME: Mysterious Milk
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Milk with a thick taste that can be gained from the monster "Goblin" in the "Fairyland" etc. There is also a rumor that it's the sap of big trees.

m_vList.NAME: Uncanny Liquid
m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] A mysterious substance that can be gained only for a limited time. It's a rare material that can be used to make Eyepatches.

m_vList.NAME: Cooling Oil
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Oil that feels cold when it touches the skin. It's dropped by the "[Boom] Hobgoblins" in the Super Test. Be careful not to put on too much of it.

m_vList.NAME: Ancient Water
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Water that contains the substance of ancient times. It can only be gathered after freezing the water in the "Mermaid Rock".

m_vList.NAME: Puniball
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A bouncy blue lump that can be gained from monsters such as "Puni Punis".

m_vList.NAME: Gelatine
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Sticky liquid that can be gained from monsters such as "Puni Punis".

m_vList.NAME: Giant Puniball
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An item dropped with a small chance by the monster "Giant Puni" that appears above 10F of the "Glittering Hill" in Fairyland etc.

m_vList.NAME: White Puniball
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A bouncy white lump that can be gained from the monsters in Eruleum such as "White Punis". It's also an all-round food ingredient!

m_vList.NAME: Red Puniball
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A bouncy red lump that can be gained from the monsters in Ribrum such as "Red Punis". It's also an all-round food ingredient!

m_vList.NAME: Yellow Puniball
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A bouncy yellow lump that can be gained from the monsters in Ateria such as "Yellow Punis". It's also an all-round food ingredient!

m_vList.NAME: Giant Red Puniball
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An item dropped with a small chance by the monster "Giant Red Puni" that appears on 20F of the "Glittering Hill" in Fairyland etc.

m_vList.NAME: Giant Yellow Puniball
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An item dropped with a small chance by the monster "Giant Yellow Puni" that appears on 30F of the "Glittering Hill" in Fairyland etc.

m_vList.NAME: Foxglove Leaf
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A herb that has been used as a medicine since ancient times. It can be gathered from the grass in the "Glittering Hill" in Fairyland etc.

m_vList.NAME: Fresh Leaf
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A herbal medicine that can fight off drowsiness. It can be gathered from the blooming flowers in Ribrum etc.

m_vList.NAME: Red Treant's Leaf
m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] An ingredient for special items. It's a special material dropped by Autumn Treants.

m_vList.NAME: Big Leaf
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A very large leaf dropped by the "[Boom] Prince Lanterns" in the Super Trial etc.

m_vList.NAME: Fragaria Leaf
m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] A special material that can be gathered in the dungeon "Fairyland of Flowers" or gained from the Ambrosia sisters.

m_vList.NAME: Rose Petal
m_vList.DESC: [Material] The fragrance of roses can calm people down. It's can also be used for skin care. It can be gathered from the blooming flowers in Ribrum.

m_vList.NAME: Cowslip
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A yellow heart-shaped flower that can be found in pastures etc. It's a raw material for making new items.

m_vList.NAME: Gorse
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A yellow flower protected by sharp thorns that can be gathered from grass in the "Rupes Deserted Mine" in Ateria.

m_vList.NAME: Taun
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A very familiar plant that is often used to make magic potions. It can be gathered from the blooming flowers in Ateria etc.

m_vList.NAME: Water Lily
m_vList.DESC: [Material] It can be gathered from the blooming flowers at the waterside in Albus etc.

m_vList.NAME: Dark Lily
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A black lily dyed in jet black that can be gathered from the blooming flowers in Ateria.

m_vList.NAME: White Flower
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A pure white flower dropped by the "[Boom] Prince Lanterns" in the Super Trial etc. It has a very fragrant smell.

m_vList.KANA: フラガリアノハナビラ
m_vList.NAME: Fragaria Petal
m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] A special material that can be gathered in the dungeon "Fairyland of Flowers" or gained from the Ambrosia sisters.

m_vList.NAME: Japanese Ash Branch
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Resilient wood that can be gathered from the trees in Albus etc. It's a material for weapons or other items.

m_vList.NAME: Willow Branch
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A very lightweight and tractable branch that can be gathered from the trees in the "Glittering Hill" in Fairyland etc.

m_vList.NAME: Japanese Red Elder
m_vList.DESC: [Material] The wood is considered as the shelter for good fairies and is said to ward off evil. It can be gathered from the trees in Ateria etc.

m_vList.NAME: Branch of Big Trees
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An item dropped with a small chance by the monster "Apple Treeman" that appears on 30F of the "Ward of Brambles" in Ribrum.

m_vList.NAME: Treant's Branch
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An item dropped with a small chance by the monster "Treant" that appears on 10F of the "Ward of Brambles" in Ribrum.

m_vList.NAME: Red Treant's Branch
m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] An ingredient for special items. It's a special material dropped by Autumn Treants.

m_vList.NAME: Fragaria Branch
m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] A special material that can be gathered in the dungeon "Fairyland of Flowers" or gained from the Ambrosia sisters.

m_vList.NAME: Mandragora Root
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A human-shaped plant that can be gathered from the trees in the "Glittering Hill" in Fairyland etc.

m_vList.NAME: Willow Root
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A very lightweight and tractable root that can be gathered from the trees in the "Glittering Hill" in Fairyland etc.

m_vList.NAME: Root of Big Trees
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An item dropped with a small chance by the monster "Ent" that appears on 20F of the "Ward of Brambles" in Ribrum.

m_vList.NAME: Red Treant's Root
m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] An ingredient for special items. It's a special material dropped by Autumn Treants.

m_vList.NAME: Bamboo
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A plant that is both durable and flexible. It's often used to make gear and buildings because of its toughness and suppleness.

m_vList.NAME: Bamboo Shoot
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Newly born bamboo. Different from bamboo, it's often used as a food ingredient.

m_vList.NAME: Egg
m_vList.DESC: [Material] The egg of a bird that lives in the forest, nutritious and often used for cooking. It can be gathered from the trees in Ribrum etc.

m_vList.NAME: Frog Egg
m_vList.DESC: [Material] It can be gathered from the frogs on the field of Albus on rainy days. Go find it when it rains.

m_vList.NAME: Mushroom
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A commonly eaten mushroom that can be gathered in Ribrum etc.

m_vList.NAME: Yadokutake
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A highly poisonous mushroom that can be gathered in Ribrum etc. It's often used to synthesize poisonous items.

m_vList.NAME: Fairy Butter
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A mushroom that can be gathered in Fairyland etc. Its name comes from its unique sweetness.

m_vList.NAME: Mudhead
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A fast-growing mushroom whose name comes from the fact that a fallen person will put on dirt. It can be gathered in Ateria etc.

m_vList.NAME: Electric Mushroom
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A mushroom that resembles an edible mushroom but is actually dangerous. It can be gathered in Ribrum etc. and is often used to synthesize medicine etc.

m_vList.NAME: Deodorant Moss
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A plant with a deodorizing effect that can also be used as the material for household medicine. It can be gathered in humid areas.

m_vList.NAME: Ghost-Laugh Mushroom
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A mushroom that can make the people who eat it keep laughing. It can be gathered in the "Rupes Deserted Mine" in Ateria etc.

m_vList.NAME: Fluffy Feather
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A soft feather often used for clothing decoration. It can be gathered from the birds on the field of Albus etc.

m_vList.NAME: Angel's Feather
m_vList.DESC: [Special Material] A mysterious material gained from the Dimensional Vortex. It's an ingredient for the Angel gear.

m_vList.NAME: Flight Feather
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A feather used for clothing decoration. It's dropped by the birds often seen in Eruleum.

m_vList.NAME: Phoenix's Feather
m_vList.DESC: [Material] The feather of a rare bird. It's often used to make special gear.

m_vList.NAME: Cod
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A fish with very little fat and a refreshing taste that can be caught in Ribrum etc. It's very delicious when fried.

m_vList.NAME: Salmon
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A fish with the habit of returning to its river of birth during its spawning season. It's a popular food loved by many people.

m_vList.NAME: Shrimp
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An aquatic animal with a shell. It's characterized by its tight taste and sweetness. It's a popular food loved by many people.

m_vList.NAME: Ancient Fish
m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] A fish that can be found in Ribrum. It is said that it has been living for a long time without changing its appearance.

m_vList.NAME: Fish Scale
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A small scale gained from the fish caught in Albus etc. They can also be processed by being tied together.

m_vList.NAME: Dragon Scale
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A very hard scale that all adventurers over the world want. It's a material with high heat resistance.

m_vList.NAME: Snake's Shed Skin
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A material that resembles shed snake skin. It's dropped by the "Nuckelavees" on 10F of the "Undersea Shrine" in Eruleum etc.

m_vList.NAME: Beast Meat
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Meat appropriately cut from wild beasts. It can be gained from the monsters that appear during night hours, such as "Wolves".

m_vList.NAME: Fresh Meat
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Fresh meat dropped by the Sea Mink that appears in the "Undersea Shrine" in Eruleum etc.

m_vList.NAME: Marbled Meat
m_vList.DESC: [Material] High-quality fat marbled meat. It's often used to make sumptuous dishes at grand occasions such as the Harvest Festival.

m_vList.NAME: Wild Liver
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A wild beast liver with a rich wild taste. It can be gained from the monsters that appear during night hours such as "Wolves".

m_vList.NAME: Uni
m_vList.DESC: [Attack] An urchin-shaped plant that can be gathered in forests. It can be used as an attack item.

m_vList.NAME: Poisonous Uni
m_vList.DESC: [Attack] A poisonous urchin-shaped attack item that is an improved version of the Uni. It has a certain chance to poison the enemy.

m_vList.NAME: Numbing Uni
m_vList.DESC: [Attack] A stinging urchin-shaped attack item that is an improved version of the Uni. It has a certain chance to paralyze the enemy.

m_vList.NAME: Black Uni
m_vList.DESC: [Attack] An attack item that splashes black liquid when thrown and is an improved version of the Uni. It has a certain chance to inflict "Blindness" on the enemy.

m_vList.NAME: Frightening Uni
m_vList.DESC: [Attack] An improved version of the Uni which is packed with various dangerous items. It has various effects such as scaring enemies with a certain chance.

m_vList.NAME: Uni Pouch
m_vList.DESC: [Attack] An improved bag packed with Unis. It's likely to deal higher damage than the Uni.

m_vList.NAME: Big Uni Pouch
m_vList.DESC: [Attack] A bag packed with Unis. It's likely to deal higher damage than the Uni Pouch.

m_vList.NAME: Acorn
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A nut that can be gathered in forests. It smells and tastes good when cooked with other food such as wheat.

m_vList.NAME: Walnut
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A fruit with a hard shell that can be gathered from the trees in Albus etc.

m_vList.NAME: Olive
m_vList.DESC: [Material] The ripe fruit of olive trees. It's often used as cooking oil as it contains lots of oil.

m_vList.NAME: Hawthorn
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A red berry dropped by the "[Boom] Hobgoblins" in the Super Test etc. Don't get its juice on cloth as it's hard to wash off.

m_vList.NAME: Green Apple
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A fruit used to make juice or jam. It can be gathered from the apple trees in Albus etc.

m_vList.NAME: Fully-Ripe Apple
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A fully-ripe apple with sweet juice which can be gathered from the apple trees in Albus etc.

m_vList.NAME: Golden Apple
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A beautiful apple that gives off a golden glow. It smells sweet, but it feels like it's inedible.

m_vList.NAME: Muscat
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A fruit used to make desserts or juice. It can be gathered from the grape vines in Ribrum etc.

m_vList.NAME: Fully-Ripe Grape
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A bunch of sweet and juicy fully-ripe grapes that have already turned purple. It can be gathered from the grape vines in Ribrum etc.

m_vList.NAME: Plum
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A soft, sour and sweet fruit used to make wine or desserts. It can be gathered from the trees in Ateria etc.

m_vList.NAME: Peach
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A pink, juicy and sweet fruit used to make wine or desserts. It's often seen in Fairyland etc.

m_vList.NAME: Orange
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A fruit planted in Eruleum for its resistance to sea wind. It's often used to make desserts.

m_vList.NAME: Carrot
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A vegetable of the cabbage family that grows at the base of a tree. It's often used as a cooking ingredient.

m_vList.NAME: Potato
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A vegetable that can be gathered from the grass in Ribrum etc. Potato pies are often served in meals.

m_vList.NAME: Lettuce
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A vegetable that can be used to cook various kinds of dishes. It's said that it can also be used as a medicine.

m_vList.NAME: Pumpkin
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A green and yellow vegetable that is rich in vitamins. It can also be gained from the pumpkin monsters in Ateria etc.

m_vList.NAME: Comfrey
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A plant with pale red and bell-shaped flowers that can be gathered from the grass in the "Rupes Deserted Mine" in Ateria.

m_vList.NAME: Mussel
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A blue-black triangular shell that is characterized by its high nutritional value and soft flesh.

m_vList.NAME: Sea Star
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A star-shaped shell. It can be caught from the fish pool by the sea that only appears at night, or the fish pool in the "Mermaid Rock" etc.

m_vList.NAME: Sharp Hair
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A pointed body hair that can be gathered from the small animals in Eruleum etc. In some areas, it's used for clothing decoration.

m_vList.NAME: Bright-Colored Hair
m_vList.DESC: [Material] A hair from the head of otters. It still shines golden after falling out and is often used to make gear and items.

m_vList.NAME: Fluffy Fur
m_vList.DESC: [Material] The fur dropped by the rabbits inhabiting Ribrum. Chase them when you see them on the field.

m_vList.DESC: [Special Material] A mysterious material gained from the Dimensional Vortex. It's an ingredient for the Lionic gear.

m_vList.NAME: Beast Skin
m_vList.DESC: [Material] Durable fur that can be gained from the monsters that appear during night hours such as "Wolves".

m_vList.DESC: [Event Material] A necessary ingredient that can be used to make the "Halloween☆Cosplay" gear "Wolf Cap".

m_vList.DESC: [Material] A bone gained from the Ooze monsters inhabiting Albus. The ring made from this kind of bone is very popular.

m_vList.NAME: Giant's Bone
m_vList.DESC: [Material] In a word, it is a huge and strong bone. It can be shaved and used to make gear.

m_vList.NAME: Rotten Bone
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An old bone that can be gained from the "Skeletons" living in the "Hideout of the Dardala Company" in Ateria etc.

m_vList.DESC: [Material] A broken sword that can be found everywhere. It can be repaired and reused to make gear.

m_vList.DESC: [Material] An item dropped with a small chance by the monster "Blue Cap" that appears on 20F of the "Goblins' Den" in Albus.

m_vList.NAME: Scrap Iron
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An item dropped with a small chance by the monster "Red Cap" that appears on 10F of the "Goblins' Den" in Albus.

m_vList.NAME: Forging Hammer
m_vList.DESC: [Ingredient] A hammer made for a friend who leaves the atelier. There is no particular use.

m_vList.NAME: Round Feces
m_vList.DESC: [Material] The feces dropped by the rabbits inhabiting Albus or Ribrum etc. Chase them when you see them on the field.

m_vList.NAME: Broken Stick
m_vList.DESC: [Material] An item dropped with a small chance by the monster "Hobgoblin" that appears on 30F of the "Goblins' Den" in Albus.

m_vList.NAME: Philosopher's Stone
m_vList.DESC: [Ingredient] One of the ingredients considered to be the gateway to become a top alchemist. It cannot be created with only ordinary knowledge and efforts.
